# MCP Framework Guide

## Core Components
The MCP (Model-Controller-Presenter) framework consists of several key components:

### Server Components
- [MCPServer.php](mdc:src/MCP/Core/MCPServer.php) - Base server implementation
- [AgenticServer.php](mdc:src/MCP/Core/AgenticServer.php) - Agent management server

### Agent Components
- [ServiceHealthAgent.php](mdc:src/MCP/Core/ServiceHealthAgent.php) - Service health monitoring
- [DeploymentAutomationAgent.php](mdc:src/MCP/Core/DeploymentAutomationAgent.php) - Deployment automation

### Service Layer
- [AuditLogger.php](mdc:src/MCP/Core/Services/AuditLogger.php) - Audit logging service
- [AccessControl.php](mdc:src/MCP/Core/Services/AccessControl.php) - Access control service
- [TaskManager.php](mdc:src/MCP/Core/Services/TaskManager.php) - Task management service

## Testing Structure
The test suite is organized as follows:

### Unit Tests
- [BaseTestCase.php](mdc:tests/Unit/MCP/Core/BaseTestCase.php) - Base test case for core components
- [BaseAgenticTestCase.php](mdc:tests/Unit/MCP/Agentic/BaseAgenticTestCase.php) - Base test case for agentic components

### Test Runners
- [CoreTestRunner.php](mdc:tests/Unit/MCP/Core/CoreTestRunner.php) - Core component test runner
- [AgenticTestRunner.php](mdc:tests/Unit/MCP/Agentic/AgenticTestRunner.php) - Agentic component test runner

## Development Guidelines
1. All new agents must extend the base Agent class
2. Services must implement the ServiceInterface
3. Tests must follow the established test plan in [test_plan.md](mdc:.reports/test_plan.md)
4. Code must comply with PSR-12 standards
5. All changes must be covered by unit tests
